node.text:
COMPETITION TIME! 💙🎁
In continuation and celebration of our beautiful ocean, we have partnered with @aquatech_imagingsolutions to host an ocean photo competition for a chance to win a $500 gift card from AquaTech!
To enter simply post one of your own original photographs that best represents what the ocean means to you. In the caption mention @Aquatech_imagingsolutions and @ocean plus use the hashtag #atoceancomp to have your photo enter the draw. The competition is open from ‪June 8-21‬, images can be captured on any device and multiple entries are accepted as long as posted from the 8th of June 2020. Our favourite images will have the chance to be featured on both AquaTech's and Ocean's Instagram pages with the final winner announced here ‪on June 24th.‬ Our winner will be chosen by a judging panel made up of ocean photographers @davesandford, @caitmiersphotography & @thurstonphoto.

For the full terms and conditions visit the link in our bio. #worldoceansday2020 #atoceancomp #aquatech
.
.
.
.This promotion is in no way sponsored, endorsed or administered by, or associated with Instagram.
.
Video Credit:
@nolanomura
@davesandford
@thurstonphoto
@benjhicks

node.text:
We’ve joined with @sealegacy & @global_wildlife_conservation to share this unique and important perspective on the current state of our world.

#ExtinctionEndsHere

What comes after the Pandemic? This video message from the virus to humankind is a chilling reminder that our future is intimately connected with all other life on Earth. We know where the pandemic came from, and we know how to stop the next one. It's time to make our voices heard. Enough is enough. Now that our own vulnerability has been laid bare, it's time to demand #ExtinctionEndsHere -- for all life on Earth.

TAKE ACTION: ExtinctionEndsHere.org

Video: @SeaLegacy & @global_wildlife_conservation.

@shawnheinrichs @paulnicklen @mitty 💙

node.text:
Whether you surf or not, taming these walls of water is something to behold!
There have been some insane waves hitting Tahiti in the last 24hrs. Local legends @matahidrollet and his brother @manoa_drollet waited 9 hours without taking one wave out the back of the Teahupoo line up. At 5 pm this evening they finally went and scored the Bomb of the Friday 13 th Swell. 
Patience pays off.  Video @timmckenna shared via @juansharks 🌊💙

node.text:
Serene moments from @dolphindronedom to lift your spirit, the world is STILL a beautiful place!

“I used to dream at night about what I would do if I had my own boat. I’d picture this serene, impossible scenario of peacefully drifting away during a perfect sunset with the only sound breaking the silence being the exhale of the largest animal on earth. Somehow I’ve been fortunate enough to have lived that very same fairytale a handful of times, but I’ve never really been able to capture it on camera as a drone operator. Now that I’m branching out into other realms of cinematography, I’m able to share these amazing moments with you too! I hope to share many more fairytale evenings with you all!” 💙

node.text:
A picture of pure freedom.. from @dolphindronedom 🐬 
•
Having become so specialized in cinematography and drone work, I rarely get to pull out my regular camera anymore. However, when the dolphins start flying I do genuinely enjoy traditional photography! This shot was taken only a week after I launched @gonewhalewatching in September of 2019. @jbunz was pretty much my only guest that was booking during this period, and these sunset trips are still some of my favorite trips I’ve ever done. Now 2 years later Jen is one of our company’s best photographers, and this photo is hanging in my home as perhaps my favorite shot I’ve ever taken!
